article.description: — Honor Huff's 24 points helped Chattanooga defeat Alabama A&M 88-72 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Huff scores 24 as Chattanooga beats Alabama A&M 88-72
article.linkText: Huff scores 24 as Chattanooga beats Alabama A&M 88-72
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Ala. -- — Honor Huff's 24 points helped Chattanooga defeat Alabama A&M 88-72 on Saturday night. Huff shot 7 for 15 (6 for 11 from 3-point range) and 4 of 5 from the free throw line for the Mocs (7-3). Myles Che added 16 points while going 5 of 7 from the floor, including 1 for 3 from 3-point range, and 5 for 6 from the line, and they also had five assists. Trey Bonham was 4 of 7 shooting, including 2 for 4 from 3-point range, and went 4 for 6 from the line to finish with 14 points. Dailin Smith finished with 19 points for the Bulldogs (1-10). Cameron Tucker added 10 points and five assists for Alabama A&M. Anthony Bryant also had 10 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
